<map id="Entity Relationship Diagram" name="Entity Relationship Diagram">
<area shape="rect" id="node1" title="dsgrid.config.dimensions.AnnualTimeDimensionModel

Defines an annual time dimension where timestamps are years.

Attributes:
 &#160;&#160;&#160;name (str): Dimension name
 &#160;&#160;&#160;display_name (str): Display name. Source for auto&#45;generated dimension_query_name.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;dimension_query_name (Optional[str]): Auto&#45;generated query name for SQL queries. Default is None.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;dimension_type (DimensionType(DSGEnum)): Type of the dimension
 &#160;&#160;&#160;dimension_id (Optional[str]): Unique identifier, generated by dsgrid. Default is None.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;version (Optional[str]): Version, generated by dsgrid. Default is None.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;module (Optional[str]): Python module with the dimension class. Default is &#39;dsgrid.dimension.standard&#39;.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;class_name (str): Dimension record model class name
 &#160;&#160;&#160;cls (Optional[Any]): Dimension record model class. Default is None.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;description (str): A description of the dimension records that is helpful, memorable, and identifiable
 &#160;&#160;&#160;id (Optional[str]): Registry database ID. Default is None.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;key (Optional[str]): Registry database key. Default is None.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;rev (Optional[str]): Registry database revision. Default is None.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;measurement_type (MeasurementType(DSGEnum)): 
 &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;The type of measurement represented by a value associated with a timestamp:
 &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;mean, min, max, measured, total. Default is MeasurementType.TOTAL.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;str_format (Optional[str]): Timestamp string format. Default is &#39;%Y&#39;.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;ranges (List[TimeRangeModel]): Defines the contiguous ranges of time in the data, inclusive of start and end time.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;include_leap_day (bool): Whether annual time includes leap day. Default is False.
" alt="" coords="2111,1717,2659,2249"/>
<area shape="rect" id="node2" title="dsgrid.config.dimensions.TimeRangeModel

Defines a continuous range of time.

Attributes:
 &#160;&#160;&#160;start (str): First timestamp in the data
 &#160;&#160;&#160;end (str): Last timestamp in the data (inclusive)
" alt="" coords="3143,1877,3337,1961"/>
<area shape="rect" id="node3" title="dsgrid.config.dimensions.DateTimeDimensionModel

Defines a time dimension where timestamps translate to datetime objects.

Attributes:
 &#160;&#160;&#160;name (str): Dimension name
 &#160;&#160;&#160;display_name (str): Display name. Source for auto&#45;generated dimension_query_name.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;dimension_query_name (Optional[str]): Auto&#45;generated query name for SQL queries. Default is None.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;dimension_type (DimensionType(DSGEnum)): Type of the dimension
 &#160;&#160;&#160;dimension_id (Optional[str]): Unique identifier, generated by dsgrid. Default is None.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;version (Optional[str]): Version, generated by dsgrid. Default is None.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;module (Optional[str]): Python module with the dimension class. Default is &#39;dsgrid.dimension.standard&#39;.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;class_name (str): Dimension record model class name
 &#160;&#160;&#160;cls (Optional[Any]): Dimension record model class. Default is None.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;description (str): A description of the dimension records that is helpful, memorable, and identifiable
 &#160;&#160;&#160;id (Optional[str]): Registry database ID. Default is None.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;key (Optional[str]): Registry database key. Default is None.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;rev (Optional[str]): Registry database revision. Default is None.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;time_type (TimeDimensionType(DSGEnum)): 
 &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Type of time dimension:
 &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;datetime, annual, representative_period, noop. Default is TimeDimensionType.DATETIME.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;measurement_type (MeasurementType(DSGEnum)): 
 &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;The type of measurement represented by a value associated with a timestamp:
 &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;mean, min, max, measured, total. Default is MeasurementType.TOTAL.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;str_format (Optional[str]): Timestamp string format. Default is &#39;%Y&#45;%m&#45;%d %H:%M:%s&#39;.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;frequency (timedelta): Resolution of the timestamps
 &#160;&#160;&#160;ranges (List[TimeRangeModel]): Defines the continuous ranges of time in the data, inclusive of start and end time.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;leap_day_adjustment (Optional[LeapDayAdjustmentType(DSGEnum)]): Leap day adjustment method applied to time data. Default is LeapDayAdjustmentType.NONE.
 &#160;&#160;&#160;time_interval_type (TimeIntervalType(DSGEnum)): The range of time that the value associated with a timestamp represents, e.g., period&#45;beginning
 &#160;&#160;&#160;timezone (TimeZone(DSGEnum)): 
 &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Time zone of data:
 &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;UTC,
 &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;HawaiiAleutianStandard,
 &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;AlaskaStandard, AlaskaPrevailing,
 &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;PacificStandard, PacificPrevailing,
 &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;MountainStandard, MountainPrevailing,
 &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;CentralStandard, CentralPrevailing,
 &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;EasternStandard, EasternPrevailing,
" alt="" coords="2041,1054,2729,1670"/>
<area shape="rect" id="node4" title="dsgrid.config.dimensions.DimensionModel

Defines a non&#45;time dimension

